 Job Description and Requirements 
 We are looking for a successful candidate to be a senior software developer in a new product area within Synopsysâ€™ Digital Design Group Business Unit in the area of 3- Dimensional ICs. This individual will be responsible for leading and helping us define the product architecture and leading integration with our state of the art digital implementation and signoff flows, designing highly efficient data structures and algorithms, and a commitment to deliver top quality production software which exceeds customer expectations. 
 
This role calls for an experienced and highly skilled software developer that understands how to analyze EDA tool and flow problems, and works with key customers as well as cutting edge industry partners to define and propose novel solutions for the 3DIC design space. This person will help architect new solutions that enable customers to solve the complexity and capacity challenges of new advanced Multi-Die designs. 
Knowledge/Experience required: EDA software development, design of algorithms with efficient data structures, 3DIC design 
Has strong motivation to learn and explore new technologies and demonstrates good analysis and problem-solving skills. 
Working knowledge in developing and maintaining complex C++/C applications in a Unix/Linux environment. 
Attentive to stringent performance and quality requirements. 
Knowledge of EDA design tool implementation and signoff flows 
Strong communication skills, verbal and written. Ability to produce design documents detailing product requirements. 
MS/Phd in EE, CS, CE or related discipline and 15+ years of industry experience. 
 
